answerText: Death of a Naturalist [10] This Irish poet of Death of a Naturalist also wrote The Haw Lantern and Wintering Out, but is probably best known for his translation of Beowulf.

question: Question: The line "A four foot box, a foot for every year" ends this collection's poem about the death of the poet's young brother Christopher, "Mid-Term Break." 10 points each: [10] Name this poetry collection which also includes "Digging" as well as a title poem in which the speaker recounts observing the frogs at a flax-dam.
